post content: b'Hi all, I have closed the original thread in the chill out cafe and created two "describe how you feel with a sentence" threads. A new one in the chillout cafe and another in experiences.The aim of the chill out cafe has always been for some time out from mental health struggles and a bit of light hearted "banter" so is therefore not the right place to express mental health struggles/ emotional distress. Everyone needs and deserves support so if you don\'t want to start your own thread or just need a short vent then this thread can be that place.'

b"Shattered, scared, shaky, in a nightmare situation, feeling my brain is an exploding melon, and holding on to life in a dying body. b"I am feeling low and tense,dismayed by other people's depressive take on the world of psychiatry and mental illness,it is as if we can't be in our own power until the system is perfect and being run the way it should be.Why can't people see it is up to each one of us as individuals to reach for the change we want from the system and affect that in any way we can.If we are being oppressed it is because we are consenting to it in some way.That may be by just giving up or complying out of fear of losing what we already have.If you are going to give up and hang your head in resignation then do it but stop the endless whining and complaining as well.It only brings those who are making internal changes and therefore effecting external changes to the system of psychiatry right down and ties them in to an unchanging status quo as well.In other words if you think your road is blocked get off that road and on to another otherwise you are blocking the road for everyone else behind you too.And that isn't good!I 'd rather take on the system and change what I can about it than comply with it with my right hand and protest about it with my left!People are seeing it all as structure and forgetting about agency!"
